  "body": "I really liked the idea of extending the HRE to add globally available random wallets as constants. However, implementing my desired logic in TypeScript appears to be a challenge. \r\n\r\nHere's what I have in my JS `hardhat.config.js`:\r\n```js\r\n/**\r\n * @notice For `hardhat.config.js`\r\n */\r\nextendEnvironment(hre => {\r\n  const randomWallet1 = hre.ethers.Wallet.createRandom()\r\n  const randomWallet2 = hre.ethers.Wallet.createRandom()\r\n\r\n  hre.randomWallet1 = randomWallet1\r\n  hre.randomWallet2 = randomWallet2\r\n})\r\n```\r\n\r\nI attempt to do the same in TypeScript. However, when I do, TypeScript complains that that `Property 'randomWallet1' does not exist on type 'HardhatRuntimeEnvironment'.ts` and I'm not sure how to get around this without just using the JS version.\r\n\r\n### Edit:\r\n* Corrected my mistake of duplicate code",
