    "body": "When extending the `hre` in TypeScript, you need to extend the type `HardhatRuntimeEnvironment` itself too. I recommend you take a look at the [TS plugin boilerplate](https://github.com/nomiclabs/hardhat-ts-plugin-boilerplate/blob/master/src/type-extensions.ts#L28) for a complete example on how to do so.\r\n\r\nThe gist of it is that you declare a `HardhatRuntimeEnvironment` interface that includes the new fields that you want to add so that it merges with the declaration from Hardhat. Note the `declare module \"hardhat/types/runtime\"` bit. That's necessary to merge with the Hardhat type declaration.\r\n\r\nIf you're not writing a plugin, you probably don't need to strictly follow the pattern shown in the TS plugin boilerplate.",
